Rev. Roy Victor Bagley
12.8.33 ~ 29.1.14
Softly the leaves of memory fall,
Gently I gather and treasure then all,
Unseen, unheard,
You are always near,
So missed, So loved, So very dear."▐
█Philomena Mary Gilbert
1939 -2020
Originally from Limerick, Ireland,
Philomena moved to England,
Shortbutts Lane and then Upper ST John Street
and enjoyed a long career in the NHS,
working locally.
Forever in our hearts"¶
